OL,3,CFame reduces a celebrity's life
OL,4,Cexpectancy by nearly five years, study
OL,5,Csays
OL,7,FLife in the spotlight may mean
OL,8,Fparties, glamour and paparazzi, but it
OL,9,Fcould also lead to a shorter life, a
OL,10,Fstudy has found.
OL,12,FResearchers found that fame could
OL,13,Fshorten singers' life expectancy by
OL,14,Faround 4.6 years, with solo artists
OL,15,Fappearing to carry a higher risk of
OL,16,Fearly death, compared with those
OL,17,Fperforming in a band.
