OL,3,CFame reduces a celebrity's life
OL,4,Cexpectancy by nearly five years, study
OL,5,Csays
OL,7,FThe study, published in the Journal of
OL,8,FEpidemiology and Community Health,
OL,9,Fexamined data on 648 singers; half of
OL,10,Fthose examined were deemed as famous,
OL,11,Fwhile the other half had not achieved
OL,12,Fstardom.
OL,14,FAcademics matched a famous singer to a
OL,15,Fless famous singer based on certain
OL,16,Fcharacteristics, which included
OL,17,Fgender, nationality, ethnicity and
OL,18,Ftheir genre of music, as well as
OL,19,Fwhether the singer was in a band or
OL,20,Fperformed as a solo artist.
