OL,3,CFame reduces a celebrity's life
OL,4,Cexpectancy by nearly five years, study
OL,5,Csays
OL,7,FThe study found that famous singers
OL,8,Flived to an average age of 75 while
OL,9,Fless famous singers lived to 79.
OL,11,FThey also found that famous singers
OL,12,Fhad a 33% higher mortality risk
OL,13,Fcompared to those considered less
OL,14,Ffamous.
OL,16,F"The result offers new evidence
OL,17,Flinking fame with higher mortality
OL,18,Frisk," said the report's authors.
