OL,3,CFame reduces a celebrity's life
OL,4,Cexpectancy by nearly five years, study
OL,5,Csays
OL,7,F"The increased mortality risk
OL,8,Fassociated with fame is comparable to
OL,9,Fother well-known health risks, such as
OL,10,Foccasional smoking.
OL,12,F"Given that these conditions are
OL,13,Fwidely recognised as serious health
OL,14,Fthreats requiring preventive measures,
OL,15,Fthe similar impact of fame on
OL,16,Fmortality suggests that being famous
OL,17,Fis an important factor influencing
OL,18,Flongevity and underscores the need for
OL,19,Ftargeted interventions to mitigate its
OL,20,Fdetrimental effects on longevity."
